  "data": {
    "title": "Trainual Tutorial: Build Your Team's Playbook Step by Step",
    "excerpt": "Learn how to use Trainual to document processes, onboard hires fast, and scale your team with this step-by-step tutorial. Start building your playbook today.",
    "featured_image": {
      "$media": {
        "url": "https://tonyciencia.com/blog/how-to-use-trainual.jpg",
        "alt": "Trainual Tutorial: Build Your Team's Playbook Step by Step",
        "filename": "how-to-use-trainual.jpg"
      }
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "*Disclosure: This post contains affiliate links. If you sign up through our links, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have ever watched a new hire sit through three days of shadowing, asking the same questions ten different people already answered last month, you know the pain. Processes live in someone's head. Onboarding docs are scattered across Google Drive folders nobody can find. And every time a key employee takes a vacation, half the office panics.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Trainual solves that mess. It is a documentation and onboarding platform where you build your company's playbook—SOPs, training modules, role descriptions, policies—all in one searchable, assignable hub. Think of it as the operating manual your business never had.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This tutorial walks you through every step, from account creation to a fully functional team playbook. By the end, you will have a repeatable system that makes hiring, training, and scaling feel almost automatic.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-trainual"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you want the big-picture overview first, check out ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "what Trainual is and how it works",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 1: Create Your Account and Pick a Plan",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://start.trainual.com/f7efdn8x5gwx-rul9tm"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Head to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "trainual.com",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and start a free trial. Trainual does not ask for a credit card upfront, which I appreciate—it lets you poke around before committing.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You will answer a few onboarding questions about your company size and industry. Trainual uses this to suggest templates and structure, so do not skip them. Even if the suggestions are not perfect, they give you a skeleton to start with.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Plans scale by team size. The essentials tier covers the core features: document creation, assignments, tracking. Higher tiers add things like custom branding, priority support, and advanced permissions. For most small to mid-size teams, the standard plan is plenty.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Once you land inside the dashboard, take five minutes to explore. The interface is clean—left sidebar for navigation, center area for content, top bar for search and settings. No labyrinth of menus. No \"where did that feature go?\" moments.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 2: Build Your Company Foundation",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Before writing a single SOP, set up your organizational structure. This is the backbone of your playbook.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Navigate to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Company",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " in the sidebar. Here you will define:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Roles and positions.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " List every role in your company, from CEO to intern. Each role gets its own page where you will later attach relevant training and procedures.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Departments or teams.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Group roles logically. Sales, Operations, Engineering, whatever fits your org chart.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "People.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Invite team members by email. They get a welcome link and land inside their own personalized dashboard showing exactly what they need to learn.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This structure matters because Trainual uses it to assign content intelligently. When you tag a piece of training to a role, every person in that role sees it automatically. No manual assignment needed for new hires—onboarding becomes self-serve.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 3: Document Your Processes (SOPs)",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Now the real work begins. Click ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Processes",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and start building your standard operating procedures.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Trainual gives you a rich text editor that supports:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Headings, bullet lists, numbered steps",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Embedded images and videos (upload directly or paste a Loom/YouTube link)",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "File attachments for checklists, templates, or reference PDFs",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Inline quizzes to verify comprehension",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here is how I recommend structuring each SOP:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Title it with action language.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " \"How to Process a Refund\" beats \"Refund Policy\" every time. New hires search by what they need to *do*, not what the policy is *called*.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Start with the \"why.\"",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " One or two sentences explaining why this process exists. Context sticks better than rote instructions.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Break it into numbered steps.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Each step should be one action. If a step has three sub-actions, use a nested list.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Add visuals.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " A screenshot of the actual software screen is worth a paragraph of description.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tag it to roles.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " At the bottom of each process, assign which roles need to know it.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pro tip: start with the five processes that cause the most confusion or consume the most manager time. Do not try to document everything in week one. You will burn out. Build iteratively.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/trainual-tips"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For more advanced techniques, our ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Trainual tips and best practices guide",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " covers formatting tricks, version control, and how to keep content fresh.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 4: Create Training Subjects",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "SOPs cover *how* to do something. ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Subjects",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " cover *what* someone needs to know—company history, culture, compliance, product knowledge, tool training.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Go to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Subjects",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and create topics like:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Company Mission and Values",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Product Overview for New Sales Reps",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "GDPR Compliance Basics",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How We Use HubSpot (or whatever CRM you run)",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Each subject can contain multiple chapters. Chapters can mix reading material, video, and quizzes. Trainual tracks completion at the chapter level, so you get granular visibility into where someone stopped or struggled.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The quiz feature is underrated. You can create multiple-choice questions that appear after a chapter. If a new hire gets a question wrong, Trainual can automatically require them to re-read that section before retaking it. This is not about being punitive—it is about catching misunderstandings before they become bad habits.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I have seen companies reduce their 2-week onboarding to 5 days by moving classroom sessions into Trainual subjects. New hires complete self-paced modules before day one, then spend in-person time on hands-on practice instead of lectures. That is a massive productivity gain.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 5: Assign, Track, and Iterate",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "With content in place, go to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "My Company → Assignments",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ". This is your command center for who needs to learn what and by when.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You can assign individual pieces or entire role-based bundles. Set due dates. Trainual sends automatic reminders so you do not have to chase people down. As a manager, you see a completion dashboard showing percentage progress across your team.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Some practical uses:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "New hire onboarding bundle.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Assign all foundational subjects and SOPs with a due date of \"first 5 days.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Quarterly compliance refresh.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Re-assign updated policy documents every 90 days with a quiz to confirm understanding.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Role change training.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " When someone gets promoted, assign the new role's bundle so they ramp up independently.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The tracking data surfaces something powerful: *where your documentation is weak.* If 60% of your team fails a quiz question, the problem is not your team—it is how you explained the concept. Go back, rewrite that section, add a video, try again. Trainual turns your playbook into a living document that improves with use.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/trainual-use-cases"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For real-world examples of teams using this workflow, check out ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "these Trainual use cases",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ".",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "New and Standout Features",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Trainual ships updates regularly. A few recent additions worth highlighting:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "AI-powered content assistant.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Staring at a blank SOP page? Trainual's AI can generate a first draft from a simple prompt. You describe the process in plain language, and it produces a structured, step-by-step document you edit and refine. This cuts authoring time dramatically.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Org chart visualization.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " Trainual now renders your roles and reporting structure as an interactive org chart. New hires can see exactly where they fit and who to go to for what. It updates automatically as you add or reassign roles.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Embeddable trainings.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " You can embed Trainual content into external sites or intranets. Useful if your team already lives in Notion, SharePoint, or a company wiki.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Mobile app improvements.",
            "marks": [
